NAME
    insert - create a single record

SYNOPSIS
    insert <model> [field=value ...]
    insert <model> '<json>'
    echo '<json>' | insert <model>
    insert . [field=value ...]

DESCRIPTION
    Creates a single new record in the specified model. Records can be
    created by specifying field=value pairs on the command line, or by
    piping a JSON object to stdin.

    Use "." to insert into the current collection when in /api/data/<model>.

    For bulk inserts, use insert_bulk instead.

OPTIONS
    field=value
        Set a field value. Can be repeated for multiple fields.
        Values are parsed as JSON if they look like JSON, otherwise
        treated as strings.

EXAMPLES
    insert users name="John Doe" role=user
        Create a user with inline field values

    insert users '{"name":"Bob","email":"bob@test.com"}'
        Create with inline JSON

    echo '{"name":"Bob"}' | insert users
        Create from JSON via stdin

    insert . name=Bob
        Insert into current collection (when in /api/data/users)

EXIT STATUS
    0   Success
    1   Error (model not found, validation failed, array provided, etc.)

SEE ALSO
    insert_bulk, update, delete, select, describe
